obj_root_law_sections_1:
  sectionId (35451)
  sectionNo (1)
  orderNo 1
  title `Short title and extent.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_1_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_1_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_2_00017_197445_1517807320626&sectionId=35451&sectionno=1&orderno=1&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_2_00017_197445_1517807320626
obj_root_law_sections_1_content:
  string
  line `(1) This Act may be called the Interest-tax Act, 1974.`
  line
  line `(2) It extends to the whole of India.`
obj_root_law_sections_1_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_2:
  sectionId (35452)
  sectionNo (2)
  orderNo 2
  title Definitions.
  content obj_root_law_sections_2_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_2_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_2_00017_197445_1517807320626&sectionId=35452&sectionno=2&orderno=2&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_2_00017_197445_1517807320626
obj_root_law_sections_2_content:
  string
  line `In this Act, unless the context otherwise requires,--`
  line
  line `(1) "assessee" means a person by whom interest-tax or any other sum of money is payable under this`
  line `Act and includes--`
  line
  line `(a) every person in respect of whom any proceeding under this Act has been taken for the`
  line `assessment of his chargeable interest or of the amount of refund due to him or of the chargeable`
  line `interest of any other person in respect of which he is assessable or of the amount of refund due to`
  line `such other person;`
  line
  line `(b) every person who is deemed to be an assessee in default under any provision of this Act;`
  line
  line `(2) "assessment" includes re-assessment;`
  line
  line `(3) "assessment year" means the period of twelve months commencing on the 1st day of April, every`
  line year;
  line
  line `(4) "Board" means the Central Board of Direct Taxes constituted under the Central Boards of`
  line `Revenue Act, 1963 (54 of 1963);`
  line
  line `(5) "chargeable interest" means the total amount of interest referred to in section 5, computed in the`
  line `manner laid down in section 6;`
  line
  line `^1[(5A) "credit institution" means,--`
  line
  line `(i) a banking company to which the Banking Regulation Act, 1949 (10 of 1949), applies`
  line `(including any bank or banking institution referred to in section 51 of that Act) ^2***;`
  line
  line `(ii) a public financial institution as defined in section 4A of the Companies Act, 1956 (1 of 1956);`
  line
  line `(iii) a State financial corporation established under section 3 or section 3A or an institution`
  line `notified under section 46 of the State Financial Corporations Act, 1951 (63 of 1951); and`
  line `(iv) any other financial company;`
  line
  line `(5B) "financial company" means a company, other than a company referred to in sub-clause (i), (ii)`
  line `or (iii) of clause (5A), being--`
  line
  line `(i) a hire-purchase finance company, that is to say, a company which carries on, as its principal`
  line `business, hire-purchase transactions or the financing of such transactions;`
  line
  line `(ii) an investment company, that is to say, a company which carries on, as its principal business,`
  line `the acquisition of shares, stock, bonds, debentures, debenture stock or securities issued by the`
  line `Government or a local authority, or other marketable securities of a like nature;`
  line
  line `(iii) a housing finance company, that is to say, a company which carries on, as its principal`
  line `business, the business of financing of acquisition or construction of houses, including acquisition or`
  line `development of land in connection therewith;`
  line
  line `(iv) a loan company, that is to say, a company [not being a company referred to in sub-clauses (i)`
  line `to (iii)] which carries on, as its principal business, the business of providing finance, whether by`
  line `making loans or advances or otherwise;`
  line
  line `(v) a mutual benefit finance company, that is to say, a company which carries on, as its principal`
  line `business, the business of acceptance of deposits from its members and which is declared by the`
  line `Central Government under section 620A of the Companies Act, 1956 (1 of 1956), to be a Nidhi or`
  line `Mutual Benefit Society; ^3***`
  line
  line `^4[(va) a residuary non-banking company [other than a financial company referred to in`
  line `sub-clause (i), (ii), (iii), (iv) or (v)] that is to say, a company which receives any deposit under any`
  line `scheme or arrangement, by whatever name called, in one lumpsum or in instalments by way of`
  line `contributions or subscriptions or by sale of units or certificates or other instruments or in any other`
  line `manner; or]`
  line
  line `(vi) a miscellaneous finance company, that is to say, a company which carries on exclusively, or`
  line `almost exclusively, two or more classes of business referred to in the preceding sub-clauses;]`
  line
  line `(6) "Income-tax Act" means the Income-tax Act, 1961(43 of 1961);`
  line
  line `^5(7) '"interest" means interest on loans and advances made in India and includes--`
  line
  line `(a) commitment charges on unutilised portion of any credit sanctioned for being availed of in`
  line `India; and`
  line
  line `(b) discount on promissory notes and bills of exchange drawn or made in India,`
  line
  line `but does not include--`
  line
  line `(i) interest referred to in sub-section (1B) of section 42 of the Reserve Bank of India Act,`
  line `1934 (2 of 1934);`
  line
  line `(ii) discount on treasury bills;]`
  line
  line `(8) "prescribed" means prescribed by rules made under this Act;`
  line
  line `^6* * * * *;`
  line
  line `(10) all other words and expressions used herein but not defined and defined in the Income-tax Act`
  line `shall have the meanings respectively assigned to them in that Act.`
obj_root_law_sections_2_footnotes:
  string
  line `1. Ins. by Act 49 of 1991, s. 91 (w.e.f. 1-10-1991).`
  line
  line `2. The words "or a co-operative society engaged in carrying on the business of banking not being a co-operative society`
  line `providing credit facilities to farmers or village artisans" omitted by Act 18 of 1992, s. 103 (w.e.f. 1-4-1993).`
  line
  line `3. The word "or" omitted by Act 18 of 1992, s. 103 (w.e.f 1-4-1993).`
  line
  line `4. Ins. by s. 103, ibid. (w.e.f. 1-4-1993).`
  line
  line `5. Subs. by Act 49 of 1991, s. 91, for clause (7) (w.e.f. 1-10-1991).`
  line
  line `6. Clause (9) omitted by s. 91, ibid. (w.e.f. 1-10-1991).`
obj_root_law_sections_3:
  sectionId (35453)
  sectionNo (3)
  orderNo 3
  title `Tax authorities.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_3_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_3_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_2_00017_197445_1517807320626&sectionId=35453&sectionno=3&orderno=3&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_2_00017_197445_1517807320626
obj_root_law_sections_3_content:
  string
  line `^1[(1) The income-tax authorities specified in section 116 of the Income-tax Act`
  line `shall be the interest-tax authorities for the purposes of this Act.`
  line
  line `(1A) Every such authority shall exercise the powers and perform the functions of an interest-tax`
  line `authority under this Act in respect of any person within his jurisdiction.`
  line
  line `(1B) The jurisdiction of an interest-tax authority under this Act shall be the same as he has under the`
  line `Income-tax Act by virtue of orders or directions issued under section 120 of that Act (including orders or`
  line `directions assigning the concurrent jurisdiction) or under any other provision of that Act.`
  line
  line `(1C) The interest-tax authority having jurisdiction in relation to a credit institution which has no`
  line `income assessable to income-tax under the Income-tax Act shall be the interest-tax authority having`
  line `jurisdiction in respect of the area in which that institution carries on its business or has its principal place`
  line `of business.`
  line
  line `(1D) Section 118 of the Income-tax Act and any notification issued thereunder shall apply in relation`
  line `to the control of interest-tax authorities as they apply in relation to the control of the correspondingincome-tax authorities, except to the extent to which the Board may, by notification in the Official`
  line `Gazette, otherwise direct in respect of any interest-tax authority.]`
  line
  line `(2) All officers and persons employed in the execution of this Act shall observe and follow the orders,`
  line `instructions and directions of the Board:`
  line
  line `Provided that no such orders, instructions or directions shall be issued--`
  line
  line `(a) so as to require any tax authority to make a particular assessment or to dispose of a particular`
  line `case in a particular manner; or`
  line
  line `(b) so as to interfere with the discretion of the Appellate Assistant Commissioner in the exercise`
  line `of his appellate functions.`
  line
  line `(3) Every Income-tax Officer ^2[or Assistant Commissioner ^3[ or Deputy Commissioner]] employed in`
  line `the execution of this Act shall observe and follow the orders, instructions and directions issued for his`
  line `guidance by the ^4[Director] or by the Commissioner or by the ^5[Additional Commissioner of Income-tax`
  line `or the ^6[Joint Commissioner]] within whose jurisdiction he performs his functions.`
obj_root_law_sections_3_footnotes:
  string
  line `1. Subs. by s. 92, ibid., for sub-section (1) (w.e.f. 1-10-1991).`
  line
  line `2. Ins. by Act 32 of 1994, s. 56 (w.e.f. 1-6-1994).`
  line
  line `3. Ins. by Act 21 of 1998, s. 77 (w.e.f. 1-4-1998).`
  line
  line `4. Subs. by Act 32 of 1994, s. 56, for "Director of Inspection" (w.e.f. 1-6-1994).`
  line
  line `5. Subs. by s. 56, ibid., for "Inspecting Assistant Commissioner" (w.e.f. 1-6-1994).`
  line
  line `6. Subs. by Act 21 of 1998, s. 77, for "Deputy Commissioner" (w.e.f. 1-4-1998).`
obj_root_law_sections_4:
  sectionId (35454)
  sectionNo (4)
  orderNo 4
  title `Charge of tax.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_4_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_4_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_2_00017_197445_1517807320626&sectionId=35454&sectionno=4&orderno=4&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_2_00017_197445_1517807320626
obj_root_law_sections_4_content:
  string
  line `^1[(1)] Subject to the provisions of this Act, there shall be charged on every`
  line `scheduled bank for every assessment year commencing on or after the 1st day of April, 1975, a tax (in`
  line `this Act referred to as interest-tax) in respect of its chargeable interest of the previous year at the rate of`
  line `seven per cent. of such chargeable interest:`
  line
  line `^2[Provided that the rate at which interest-tax shall be charged in respect of any chargeable interest`
  line `accruing or arising after the 31st day of March, 1983 shall be three and a half per cent. of such chargeable`
  line interest.]
  line
  line `^3[(2) Notwithstanding anything contained in sub-section (1) but subject to the other provisions of this`
  line `Act, there shall be charged on every credit institution for every assessment year commencing on and from`
  line `the 1st day of April, 1992, interest-tax in respect of its chargeable interest of the previous year at the rate`
  line `of three per cent. of such chargeable interest.]`
  line
  line `^4[Provided that the rate at which interest-tax shall be charged in respect of any chargeable interest`
  line `accruing or arising after the 31st day of March, 1997 shall be two per cent. of such chargeable interest.]`
  line
  line `^5[(3) Notwithstanding anything contained in sub-sections (1) and (2), no interest-tax shall be charged`
  line `in respect of any chargeable interest accruing or arising after the 31st day of March, 2000.]`
obj_root_law_sections_4_footnotes:
  string
  line `1. Section 4 renumbered as sub-section (1) thereof by Act 49 of 1991, s. 93 (w.e.f. 1-10-1991).`
  line
  line `2. Ins. by Act 11 of 1983, s. 43 (w.e.f. 1-4-1983).`
  line
  line `3. Ins. by Act 49 of 1991, s. 93 (w.e.f. 1-10-1991).`
  line
  line `4. Ins. by Act 26 of 1997, s. 59 (w.e.f. 1-4-1998).`
  line
  line `5. Ins. by Act 10 of 2000, s. 77 (w.e.f. 1-4-2001).`
obj_root_law_sections_5:
  sectionId (35455)
  sectionNo (5)
  orderNo 5
  title `Scope of chargeable interest.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_5_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_5_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_2_00017_197445_1517807320626&sectionId=35455&sectionno=5&orderno=5&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_2_00017_197445_1517807320626
obj_root_law_sections_5_content:
  string
  line `^1[5. Scope of chargeable interest.--Subject to the provisions of this Act, the chargeable interest of`
  line `any previous year of a credit institution shall be the total amount of interest (other than interest on loans`
  line `and advances made to other credit institutions ^2[or to any co-operative society engaged in carrying on the`
  line `business of banking)] accruing or arising to the credit institution in that previous year:`
  line
  line `Provided that any interest in relation to categories of bad or doubtful debts referred to in section 43D`
  line `of the Income-tax Act shall be deemed to accrue or arise to the credit institution in the previous year in`
  line `which it is credited by the credit institution to its profit and loss account for that year or, as the case may`
  line `be, in which it is actually received by the credit institution, whichever is earlier.]`
obj_root_law_sections_5_footnotes:
  string
  line `1. Subs. by Act 49 of 1991, s. 94, for section 5 (w.e.f. 1-10-1991).`
  line
  line `2. Ins. by Act 18 of 1992, s. 104 (w.r.e.f. 1-10-91).`
obj_root_law_sections_6:
  sectionId (35456)
  sectionNo (6)
  orderNo 6
  title `Computation of chargeable interest.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_6_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_6_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_2_00017_197445_1517807320626&sectionId=35456&sectionno=6&orderno=6&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_2_00017_197445_1517807320626
obj_root_law_sections_6_content:
  string
  line `(1) Subject to the provisions of sub-section (2), in`
  line `computing the chargeable interest of a previous year, there shall be allowed from the total amount of`
  line `interest (other than interest on loans and advances made to ^1[credit institutions] accruing or arising to the`
  line `assessee in the previous year, a deduction in respect of the amount of interest which is established to have`
  line `become a bad debt during the previous year:`
  line
  line `Provided that such interest has been taken into account in computing the chargeable interest of the`
  line `assessee of an earlier previous year and the amount has been written off as irrecoverable in the accounts`
  line `of the assessee for the previous year during which it is established to have become a bad debt.`
  line
  line `Explanation.--For the removal of doubts, it is hereby declared that in computing the chargeable`
  line `interest of a previous year, no deduction, other than the deduction specified in this sub-section, shall be`
  line `allowed from the total amount of interest accruing or arising to the assessee.`
  line
  line `(2) In computing the chargeable interest of a previous year, the amount of interest which accrues or`
  line `arises to the assesse ^2[before the 1st day of August, 1974 or ^3[during the period commencing on the 1st`
  line `day of April, 1985 and ending with the 30th day of September, 1991] shall not be taken into account.`
obj_root_law_sections_6_footnotes:
  string
  line `20. Subs. by Act 49 of 1991, s. 95, for "scheduled banks" (w.e.f. 1-10-1991).`
  line
  line `2. Subs. by Act 19 of 1978, s. 33, for "before the 1st day of August, 1974" (1-4-1978).`
  line
  line `3. Subs. by Act 49 of 1991, s. 95, for "after the 31st day of March, 1985" (w.e.f. 1-10-1991).`
obj_root_law_sections_7:
  sectionId (35457)
  sectionNo (7)
  orderNo 7
  title `Return of chargeable interest.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_7_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_7_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_2_00017_197445_1517807320626&sectionId=35457&sectionno=7&orderno=7&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_2_00017_197445_1517807320626
obj_root_law_sections_7_content:
  string
  line `^1[(I) In the case of every credit institution, its principal officer, or`
  line `where in the case of a non-resident, credit institution any person has been treated as its agent under`
  line `section 163 of the Income-tax Act, such person, shall furnish a return of the chargeable interest of the`
  line `credit institution of the previous year in the prescribed form and verified in the prescribed manner and`
  line `setting forth such other particulars as may be prescribed, before the 31st day of December of the`
  line `assessment year.`
  line
  line `(2) Without prejudice to the provisions of sub-section (1), the Assessing Officer may, before the end`
  line `of the relevant assessment year, serve a notice upon the principal officer of any credit institution, or where`
  line `in the case of a non-resident credit institution any person has been treated as its agent under section 163 of`
  line `the Income-tax Act, upon such person, requiring him to furnish within thirty days from the date of service`
  line `of the notice a return of the chargeable interest of the credit institution of the previous year in the`
  line `prescribed form and verified in the prescribed manner and setting forth such other particulars as may be`
  line prescribed.
  line
  line `(3) Any assessee who has not furnished a return within the time allowed under sub-section (1) or`
  line `sub-section (2), or having furnished a return under sub-section (1) or sub-section (2) discovers any`
  line `omission or wrong statement therein, may furnish a return or a revised return, as the case may be, at any`
  line `time ^1[before the expiry of one year from the end of the relevant assessment year or before the completion`
  line `of the assessment, whichever is earlier.]`
obj_root_law_sections_7_footnotes:
  string
  line `1. Subs. by s. 96, ibid., for sub-sections (1) and (2) (w.e.f. 1-10-1991).`
  line
  line `2. Subs. by s. 96, ibid., for "before the assessment is made" (w.e.f. 1-10-1991).`
obj_root_law_sections_8:
  sectionId (35458)
  sectionNo (8)
  orderNo 8
  title Assessment.
  content obj_root_law_sections_8_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_8_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_2_00017_197445_1517807320626&sectionId=35458&sectionno=8&orderno=8&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_2_00017_197445_1517807320626
obj_root_law_sections_8_content:
  string
  line `(1) For the purposes of making an assessment under this Act, the ^2[Assessing`
  line `Officer] may serve on any person who has furnished a return under section 7 or upon whom a notice has`
  line `been served under sub-section (2) of section 7 (whether a return has been furnished or not) a notice`
  line `requiring him on a date therein to be specified, to produce or cause to be produced such accounts or`
  line `documents or evidence as the ^1[Assessing Officer] may require for the purposes of this Act and may, from`
  line `time to time, serve further notices requiring the production of such further accounts or documents or other`
  line `evidence as he may require.`
  line
  line `(2) The ^2[Assessing Officer], after considering such accounts, documents or evidence, if any, as he`
  line `has obtained under sub-section (1) and after taking into account any relevant material which he has`
  line `gathered, shall, by an order in writing assess the chargeable interest and the amount of the interest-tax`
  line `payable on the basis of such assessment.`
  line
  line `^3[(3) If any person--`
  line
  line `(a) fails to make a return as required under sub-section (1) of section 7 and has not made a return`
  line `or a revised return under sub-section (3) of that section, or`
  line
  line `(b) fails to comply with all the terms of notice under sub-section (2) of that section,`
  line
  line `the Assessing Officer shall, after taking into account all the relevant material which he has gathered and`
  line `after giving the assessee an opportunity of being heard, make the assessment of the total chargeable`
  line `interest to the best of his judgment and determine the sum payable by the assessee on the basis of such`
  line `assessment:`
  line
  line `Provided that such opportunity shall be given by the Assessing Officer by serving a notice calling`
  line `upon the assessee to show cause, on a date and time to be specified in the notice, why the assessment`
  line `should not be completed to the best of his judgment:`
  line
  line `Provided further that it shall not be necessary to give such opportunity in a case where a notice under`
  line `sub-section (1) has been issued prior to the making of an assessment under this section.]`
obj_root_law_sections_8_footnotes:
  string
  line `1. Subs. by Act 19 of 1978, s. 33, for "before the 1st day of August, 1974" (1-4-1978).`
  line
  line `2. Subs. by s. 97, ibid., for "Income-tax Officer" (w.e.f. 1-10-1991).`
  line
  line `3. Ins. by s. 97, ibid. (w.e.f. 1-10-1991).`
obj_root_law_sections_9:
  sectionId (35459)
  sectionNo (9)
  orderNo 9
  title Self-assessment.
  content obj_root_law_sections_9_content
  footnotes `1. Subs. by Act 49 of 1991, s. 98, for section 9 (w.e.f. 1-10-1991).`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_2_00017_197445_1517807320626&sectionId=35459&sectionno=9&orderno=9&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_2_00017_197445_1517807320626
obj_root_law_sections_9_content:
  string
  line `^1[9. Self-assessment.--(1) Where interest-tax is payable on the basis of any return required to be`
  line `furnished under section 7 or section 10, after taking into account the amount of interest-tax, if any,`
  line `already paid under any provision of this Act, the assessee shall be liable to pay such interest-tax, together`
  line `with interest payable under any provision of this Act for any delay in furnishing the return or any default`
  line `or delay in payment of advance interest-tax, before furnishing the return and the return shall be`
  line `accompanied by proof of payment of such interest-tax and interest.`
  line
  line `Explanation.--Where the amount paid by the assessee under this sub-section falls short of the`
  line `aggregate of the interest-tax and interest as aforesaid, the amount so paid shall first be adjusted towards`
  line `the interest payable as aforesaid and the balance, if any, shall be adjusted towards the interest-tax payable.`
  line
  line `(2) After the assessment under section 8 has been made, any amount paid under sub-section (1) shall`
  line `be deemed to have been paid towards such assessment.`
  line
  line `(3) If any assessee fails to pay the whole or any part of interest-tax or interest or both in accordance`
  line `with the provisions of sub-section (1), he shall, without prejudice to any other consequences which he`
  line `may incur, be deemed to be an assessee in default in respect of the interest-tax or interest; or both`
  line `remaining unpaid, and all the provisions of this Act shall apply accordingly.]`
obj_root_law_sections_10:
  sectionId (35460)
  sectionNo (10)
  orderNo 10
  title `Interest escaping assessment.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_10_content
  footnotes `1. Subs. by s. 99, ibid., for "Income-Tax Officer" (w.e.f. 1-10-1991).`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_2_00017_197445_1517807320626&sectionId=35460&sectionno=10&orderno=10&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_2_00017_197445_1517807320626
obj_root_law_sections_10_content:
  string
  line If--
  line
  line `(a) the ^1[Assessing Officer] has reason to believe that by reason of the omission or failure on the`
  line `part of the assessee to make a return under section 7 for any assessment year or to disclose fully and`
  line `truly all material facts necessary for his assessment for any assessment year, chargeable interest for`
  line `that year has escaped assessment or has been under-assessed or has been made the subject of`
  line `excessive, relief under this Act, or`
  line
  line `(b) notwithstanding that there has been no omission or failure as mentioned in clause (a) on the`
  line `part of the assessee, the ^1[Assessing Officer] has, in consequence of information in his possession,`
  line `reason to believe that chargeable interest assessable for any assessment year has escaped assessment`
  line `or has been under-assessed or has been made the subject of excessive relief under this Act`
  line
  line `he may, in cases falling under clause (a), at any time, and in cases falling under clause (b), at any time`
  line `within four years of the end of that assessment year, serve on the assesee a notice containing all or any of`
  line `the requirements which may be included in a notice under section 7, and may proceed to assess or`
  line `re-assess the amount chargeable to interest-tax, and the provisions of this Act shall, so far as may be,`
  line `apply, as if the notice were a notice issued under that section.`
obj_root_law_sections_10_a:
  sectionId (35461)
  sectionNo 10A
  orderNo 11
  title `Time limit for completion of assessments and re-assessments.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_10_a_content
  footnotes `1. Ins. by s.100, ibid. (w.e.f 1-10-1991).`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_2_00017_197445_1517807320626&sectionId=35461&sectionno=10A&orderno=11&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_2_00017_197445_1517807320626
obj_root_law_sections_10_a_content:
  string
  line `^1[10A. Time limit for completion of assessments and re-assessments.--(1) No order of assessment`
  line `shall be made under section 8 at any time after the expiry of two years from the end of the assessment`
  line `year in which the interest was first assessable.`
  line
  line `(2) No order of assessment or re-assessment shall be made under section 10 after the expiry of two`
  line `years from the end of the financial year in which the notice under that section was served.`
  line
  line `(3) Notwithstanding anything contained in sub-sections (1) and (2), and order of fresh assessment in`
  line `pursuance of an order passed under section 15, section 16, section 19 or section 20, setting aside or`
  line `cancelling an assessment may be made at any time before the expiry of two years from the end of the`
  line `financial year in which the order under section 15 of section 16 is received by the Commissioner or, as the`
  line `case may be, the order under section 19 or section 20 is passed by the Commissioner.`
  line
  line `(4) The provisions of sub-sections (1) and (2) shall not apply to the assessment or re-assessment made`
  line `in consequence of, or to give effect to, any finding or direction contained in an order under section 15 or`
  line `section 16 or section 19 or section 20 of this Act or section 256 or section 260 of the Income-tax Act as`
  line `applicable to this Act by virtue of section 21 of this Act or in an order of any court in a proceeding`
  line `otherwise than by way of appeal or reference under this Act and such assessment or re-assessment may,`
  line `subject to the provisions of sub-section (3), be completed at any time.`
  line
  line `Explanation 1.--In computing the period of limitation for the purposes of this section--`
  line
  line `(i) the time taken in reopening the whole or any part of the proceeding; or`
  line
  line `(ii) the period during which the assessment proceeding is stayed by an order or injunction of any`
  line Court,
  line
  line `shall be excluded.`
  line
  line `Explanation 2.--Where, by an order referred to in sub-section (4), any interest is excluded from the`
  line `chargeable interest for an assessment year in respect of an assessee, then, an assessment of such interest`
  line `for another assessment year shall, for the purposes of section 10 and this section, be deemed to be one`
  line `made in consequence of, or to give effect to, any finding or direction contained in the said order.]`
obj_root_law_sections_11:
  sectionId (35462)
  sectionNo (11)
  orderNo 12
  title `Advance payment of interest-tax.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_11_content
  footnotes `1. Subs. by Act 49 of 1991, s. 101, for sections 11 to 13 (w.e.f. 1-10-1991).`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_2_00017_197445_1517807320626&sectionId=35462&sectionno=11&orderno=12&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_2_00017_197445_1517807320626
obj_root_law_sections_11_content:
  string
  line `^1[11. Advance payment of interest-tax.--(1) Interest-tax shall be payable in advance during the`
  line `financial year in respect of the chargeable interest for the assessment year immediately following that`
  line `financial year in accordance with the provision of this section.`
  line
  line `(2) Interest-tax shall be payable in advance in three instalments during each financial year, the due`
  line `date of, and the amount payable in, each such instalment being as specified in the following Table:`
  line
  line TABLE
  line
  line `Due date of instalment Amount payable`
  line
  line `On or before the 15th September Not less than twenty per cent. of such`
  line `interest-tax Payable in advance.`
  line
  line `On or before the 15th December Not less than fifty per cent. of such`
  line `interest-tax payable in advance, as`
  line `reduced by the amount, if any, paid in`
  line `the earlier instalment.`
  line
  line `On or before the 15th March The whole amount of such interest-tax`
  line `payable in advance as reduced by the`
  line `amount or amounts, if any, paid in the`
  line `earlier instalment or instalments:`
  line
  line `Provided that any amount paid by way of interest-tax payable in advance on or before the 31st day of`
  line `March shall also be treated as interest-tax paid in advance during the financial year ending on that day for`
  line `all the purposes of this Act.]`
obj_root_law_sections_12:
  sectionId (35463)
  sectionNo (12)
  orderNo 13
  title `Interest for default in furnishing return of chargeable interest.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_12_content
  footnotes `1. Subs. by Act 49 of 1991, s. 101, for sections 11 to 13 (w.e.f. 1-10-1991).`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_2_00017_197445_1517807320626&sectionId=35463&sectionno=12&orderno=13&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_2_00017_197445_1517807320626
obj_root_law_sections_12_content:
  string
  line `^1[12. Interest for default in furnishing return of chargeable interest.--(1) Where the return of`
  line `chargeable interest for any assessment year under sub-section (1) of section 7, or in response to a notice`
  line `under sub-section (2), of that section is furnished after the due date, or is not furnished, the assessee shall be liable to pay simple interest at the rate of two per cent. for every month or part of a month comprised`
  line `in the period commencing on the date immediately following the due date, and,--`
  line
  line `(a) where the return is furnished after the due date, ending on the date of the furnishing of the`
  line `return; or`
  line
  line `(b) where no return has been furnished, ending on the date of completion of assessment under`
  line `sub-section (3) of section 8, on the amount of the interest-tax on the chargeable interest as determined`
  line `under sub-section (2) or sub-section (3) of section 8 as reduced by the interest-tax paid in advance.`
  line
  line `Explanation 1.-- In this section, "due date" means the 31st day of December of the relevant`
  line `assessment year or, as the case may be, the date on which return in response to a notice under`
  line `sub-section (2) of section 7 is due to be filed.`
  line
  line `Explanation 2.--Where in relation an assessment year, an assessment is made for the first time under`
  line `section 10, the assessment so made shall be regarded as assessment made under sub-section (2), or, as the`
  line `case may be, sub-section (3) of section 8.`
  line
  line `Explanation 3.--For the purposes of computing the interest payable under section 9, interest-tax on`
  line `the chargeable interest declared in the return shall be deemed to be the interest-tax on total chargeable`
  line `interest determined under sub-section (2) or sub-section (3) of section 8.`
  line
  line `(2) The interest payable under sub-section (1) shall be reduced by the interest, if any, paid under`
  line `section 9 towards the interest chargeable under this section.`
  line
  line `(3) Where the return of chargeable interest for any assessment year, required by a notice under`
  line `section 10 issued after the completion of assessment under sub-section (2) or sub-section (3) of section 8`
  line `or section 10 is furnished after the expiry of the time allowed under such notice or is not furnished, the`
  line `assessee shall be liable to pay simple interest at the rate of two per cent. for every month or part of a`
  line `month comprised in the period commencing on the date immediately following the expiry of time allowed`
  line `as aforesaid, and,--`
  line
  line `(a) where the return is furnished after the expiry of the time aforesaid, ending on the date of`
  line `furnishing the return; or`
  line
  line `(b) where no return has been furnished, ending on the day of completion of the re-assessment`
  line `under section 10,`
  line
  line `on the amount by which the interest-tax on the chargeable interest as determined on the basis of such`
  line `reassessment exceeds the interest-tax on chargeable interest on the basis of earlier assessment aforesaid.`
  line
  line `(4) Where, as a result of an order under section 15 or section 17 of this Act or section 254 or section`
  line `260 or section 262 of the Income-tax Act, as applicable to this Act by virtue of section 21 of this Act, the`
  line `amount on which interest was payable under sub-section (1) or sub-section (3) has been increased or`
  line `reduced, as the case may be, the interest shall be increased or reduced accordingly, and--`
  line
  line `(i) in a case where the interest is increased, the Assessing Officer shall serve on the assessee a`
  line `notice of demand in the prescribed form specifying the sum payable and such notice of demand shall`
  line `be deemed to be a notice under section 156 of the Income-tax Act as applicable to this Act by virtue`
  line `of Section 21, and the provisions of this Act shall apply accordingly;`
  line
  line `(ii) in a case where the interest is reduced, the excess interest paid, if any, shall be refunded.`
  line
  line `(5) The provisions of this section shall apply in respect of assessments for the assessment year`
  line `commencing on the 1st day of April, 1992 and subsequent years.]`
obj_root_law_sections_12_a:
  sectionId (35464)
  sectionNo 12A
  orderNo 14
  title `Interest for default in payment of interest-tax in advance.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_12_a_content
  footnotes `1. Subs. by Act 49 of 1991, s. 101, for sections 11 to 13 (w.e.f. 1-10-1991).`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_2_00017_197445_1517807320626&sectionId=35464&sectionno=12A&orderno=14&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_2_00017_197445_1517807320626
obj_root_law_sections_12_a_content:
  string
  line `^1[12A. Interest for default in payment of interest-tax in advance.--(1) Subject to the other`
  line `provisions of this section, where in any financial year, an assessee, who is liable to pay interest-tax in`
  line `advance under section 11 has failed to pay such tax, or where the interest-tax paid in advance by such`
  line `assessee is less than ninety per cent. of the assessed interest-tax, the assessee shall be liable to pay simple`
  line `interest at the rate of two per cent. for every month or part of a month comprised in the period from the`
  line `1st day of April next following such financial year to the date of determination of chargeable interest`
  line `under sub-section (2) or, as the case may be, sub-section (3) of section 8 on an amount equal to the assessed interest-tax, or, as the case may be, on the amount by which the interest-tax payable in advance`
  line `falls short of the assessed interest-tax.`
  line
  line `Explanation 1.--In this section "assessed interest-tax" means, --`
  line
  line `(a) for the purpose of computing the interest payable under section 9, the interest-tax on the`
  line `chargeable interest as declared in the return referred to in that section;`
  line
  line `(b) in any other case, interest-tax on chargeable interest as determined under sub-section (2) or, as`
  line `the case may be, sub-section (3) of section 8.`
  line
  line `Explanation 2.--Where, in relation to an assessment year, an assessment is made for the first time`
  line `under section 10, the assessment so made shall be regarded as assessment made under sub-section (2) or,`
  line `as the case may be, sub-section (3) of section 8.`
  line
  line `(2) Where, before the date of completion of assessment under sub-section (2) or sub-section (3) of`
  line `section 8, interest-tax is paid by the assessee under section 9 or otherwise,--`
  line
  line `(i) interest shall be calculated in accordance with the foregoing provisions of this section up to the`
  line `date on which the tax is so paid, and reduced by the interest, if any, paid under section 9 towards the`
  line `interest chargeable under this section;`
  line
  line `(ii) thereafter, interest shall be calculated at the rate aforesaid on the amount by which the tax so`
  line `paid together with interest-tax paid in advance falls short of the assessed interest-tax.`
  line
  line `(3) Where, as a result of an order of reassessment under section 10, the amount on which the interest`
  line `was payable under sub-section (1) is increased, the assessee shall be liable to pay simple interest at the`
  line `rate of two per cent. for every month or part of a month comprised in the period commencing on the day`
  line `following the completion of the assessment under sub-section (2) or, as the case may be, sub-section (3)`
  line `of section 8 referred to in sub-section (1) and ending on the date of reassessment under section 10, on the`
  line `amount by which the interest-tax on the basis of the reassessment exceeds the interest-tax on the`
  line `chargeable interest determined on the basis of assessment under sub-section (2) or, as the case may be,`
  line `sub-section (3) of section 8.`
  line
  line `(4) Where, as a result of an order under section 15 or section 17 of this Act or section 254 or section`
  line `260 or section 262 of the Income-tax Act as applicable to this Act by virtue of section 21 of this Act, the`
  line `amount on which interest was payable under sub-section (1) or sub-section (3) has been increased or`
  line `reduced, as the case may be, the interest shall be increased or reduced accordingly, and--`
  line
  line `(i) in a case where the interest is increased, the Assessing Officer shall serve on the assessee a`
  line `notice of demand in the prescribed form specifying the sum payable and such notice of demand shall`
  line `be deemed to be a notice under section 156 of the Income-tax Act as applicable to this Act by virtue`
  line `of section 21 of this Act, and provisions of this Act shall apply accordingly;`
  line
  line `(ii) in a case where the interest is reduced, the excess interest paid, if any, shall be refunded.`
  line
  line `(5) The provisions of this section shall apply in respect of assessments for the assessment year`
  line `commencing on the 1st day of April, 1992 and subsequent assessment years.]`
obj_root_law_sections_12_b:
  sectionId (35465)
  sectionNo 12B
  orderNo 15
  title `Interest for deferment of interest-tax payable in advance.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_12_b_content
  footnotes `1. Subs. by Act 49 of 1991, s. 101, for sections 11 to 13 (w.e.f. 1-10-1991).`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_2_00017_197445_1517807320626&sectionId=35465&sectionno=12B&orderno=15&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_2_00017_197445_1517807320626
obj_root_law_sections_12_b_content:
  string
  line `^1[12B. Interest for deferment of interest-tax payable in advance.--(1) Where in any financial year,`
  line `the assessee who is liable to pay interest-tax in advance under section 11 has failed to pay the interest-tax`
  line `and where such tax paid by the assessee on his chargeable interest on or before the 15th day of September`
  line `is less than twenty per cent. of the interest-tax due on the returned chargeable interest or the amount of`
  line `such interest-tax paid on or before the 15th day of December is less than fifty per cent. of the tax due on`
  line `the returned chargeable interest then, the assessee shall be liable to pay simple interest at the rate of one`
  line `and one-half per cent. per month of the shortfall for a period of three months on the amount of shortfall`
  line `from twenty per cent. or; as the case may be, fifty per cent. of the interest-tax due on the returned`
  line `chargeable interest.`
  line
  line `(2) The provisions of this section shall apply in respect of assessments for the assessment year`
  line `commencing on the 1st day of April, 1992 and subsequent assessment years.]`
obj_root_law_sections_13:
  sectionId (35466)
  sectionNo (13)
  orderNo 16
  title `Penalty for concealment of chargeable interest.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_13_content
  footnotes `1. Subs. by Act 49 of 1991, s. 101, for sections 11 to 13 (w.e.f. 1-10-1991).`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_2_00017_197445_1517807320626&sectionId=35466&sectionno=13&orderno=16&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_2_00017_197445_1517807320626
obj_root_law_sections_13_content:
  string
  line `^1[13. Penalty for concealment of chargeable interest.--If the Assessing Officer or the Commissioner`
  line `(Appeals) in the course of any proceeding under this Act, is satisfied that any person has concealed the`
  line `particulars of chargeable interest or has furnished inaccurate particulars of such interest, he may direct`
  line `that such person shall pay by way of penalty, in addition to any interest-tax payable by him, a sum which`
  line `shall not be less than, but shall not exceed three times, the amount of interest-tax sought to be evaded by`
  line `reason of the concealment of particulars of his chargeable interest or the furnishing of inaccurate`
  line `particulars of such chargeable interest.]`
obj_root_law_sections_14:
  sectionId (35467)
  sectionNo (14)
  orderNo 17
  title `Opportunity of being heard.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_14_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_14_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_2_00017_197445_1517807320626&sectionId=35467&sectionno=14&orderno=17&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_2_00017_197445_1517807320626
obj_root_law_sections_14_content:
  string
  line `No order imposing a penalty under section 12 or section 13 shall`
  line `be made unless the assessee has been heard, or has been given a reasonable opportunity of being heard.`
obj_root_law_sections_14_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_15:
  sectionId (35468)
  sectionNo (15)
  orderNo 18
  title `Appeals to the Commissioner (Appeals).`
  content obj_root_law_sections_15_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_15_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_2_00017_197445_1517807320626&sectionId=35468&sectionno=15&orderno=18&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_2_00017_197445_1517807320626
obj_root_law_sections_15_content:
  string
  line `15. Appeals to the ^1[Commissioner (Appeals)].--(1) Any person objecting to the amount of`
  line `interest-tax for which he is assessed by the ^2[Assessing Officer] or denying his liability to be assessed`
  line `under this Act, or objecting to any penalty or fine imposed by the ^2[Assessing Officer], or to the amount`
  line `allowed by the ^2[Assessing Officer] by way of any relief under any provision of this Act, or to any refusal`
  line `by the ^2[Assessing Officer] to grant relief or to an order of rectification having the effect of enhancing the`
  line `assessment or reducing the refund, or to an order refusing to allow the claim made by the assessee for a`
  line `rectification under section 17, may appeal to the ^1[Commissioner (Appeals)].`
  line
  line `^3[(2) Every appeal filed on or after the 1st day of October, 1998 shall be in the prescribed form and`
  line `shall be verified in the prescribed manner and shall be accompanied by a fee of two hundred and fifty`
  line rupees.]
  line
  line `(3) An appeal shall be presented within thirty days of the following date, that is to say,--`
  line
  line `(a) where the appeal relates to assessment or penalty or fine, the date of service of the notice of`
  line `the demand relating to the assessment or penalty or fine, or`
  line
  line `(b) in any other case, the date on which the intimation of the order sought to be appealed against`
  line `is served:`
  line
  line `Provided that the ^1Commissioner (Appeals)] may admit an appeal after the expiration of the said`
  line `period if he is satisfied that the appellant had sufficient cause for not presenting it within that period.`
  line
  line `(4) The ^1[Commissioner (Appeals)] shall hear and determine the appeal and, subject to the provisions`
  line `of this Act, pass such orders as he thinks fit and such orders may include an order enhancing the`
  line `assessment or penalty:`
  line
  line `Provided that an order enhancing the assessment or penalty shall not be made unless the person`
  line `affected thereby has been given a reasonable opportunity of showing cause against such enhancement.`
  line
  line `(5) The procedure to be adopted in the hearing and determination of the appeals shall, with any`
  line `necessary modification, be in accordance with the procedure applicable in relation to income-tax.`
obj_root_law_sections_15_footnotes:
  string
  line `1. Subs. by Act 29 of 1977, s. 39 and the Fifth Schedule, for " Appellate Assistant Commissioner" (w.e.f. 1-4-1977).`
  line
  line `2. Subs. by Act 49 of 1991, s. 102, for "Income-tax Officer" (w.e.f. 1-10-1991).`
  line
  line `3. Subs. by Act 21 of 1998, s. 78, for sub-section ( 2) (w.e.f. 1-10-1998).`
obj_root_law_sections_15_a:
  sectionId (35486)
  sectionNo 15A
  orderNo 19
  title Omitted.
  content obj_root_law_sections_15_a_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_15_a_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_2_00017_197445_1517807320626&sectionId=35486&sectionno=15A&orderno=19&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_2_00017_197445_1517807320626
obj_root_law_sections_15_a_content:
  string
  line `[Appeal to the Commissioner (Appeals).] Omitted by Finance (No. 2) Act, 1991 (49 of 1991),`
  line `s. 103 (w.e.f. 1-10-1991).`
obj_root_law_sections_15_a_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_16:
  sectionId (35487)
  sectionNo (16)
  orderNo 20
  title `Appeals to Appellate Tribunal.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_16_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_16_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_2_00017_197445_1517807320626&sectionId=35487&sectionno=16&orderno=20&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_2_00017_197445_1517807320626
obj_root_law_sections_16_content:
  string
  line `(1) Any assessee aggrieved by an order passed by a`
  line `Commissioner under section 19, or an order passed by ^2[a Commissioner (Appeals)] under any provision`
  line `of this Act, may appeal to the Appellate Tribunal against such order.`
  line
  line `(2) The Commissioner may, if he objects to any order passed by the ^1[Commissioner (Appeals)]`
  line `under any provision of this Act, direct the ^3[Assessing Officer] to appeal to the Appellate Tribunal against`
  line `the order.`
  line
  line `(3) Every appeal under sub-section (1) or sub-section (2) shall be filed within sixty days of the date`
  line `on which the order sought to be appealed against is communicated to the assessee or to the`
  line `Commissioner, as the case may be.`
  line
  line `(4) The^4[Assessing Officer] or the assessee, as the case may be, on receipt of notice that an appeal`
  line `against the order of the ^5[Commissioner (Appeals)] has been preferred under sub-section (1) or`
  line `sub-section (2) by the other party may, notwithstanding that he may not have appealed against such order`
  line `or any part thereof, within thirty days of the receipt of the notice, file a memorandum of cross-objections,`
  line `verified in the prescribed manner, against any part of the order of the ^5[Commissioner (Appeals)], and`
  line `such memorandum shall be disposed of by the Appellate Tribunal as if it were an appeal presented within`
  line `the time specified in sub-section (3).`
  line
  line `(5) The Appellate Tribunal may admit an appeal or permit the filing of a memorandum of`
  line `cross-objections after the expiry of the relevant period referred to in sub-section (3) or sub-section (4), if`
  line `it is satisfied that there was sufficient cause for not presenting it within that period.`
  line
  line `(6) An appeal to the Appellate Tribunal shall be in the prescribed form and shall be verified in the`
  line `prescribed manner and, shall, except in the case of an appeal referred to in sub-section (2) or a`
  line `memorandum of cross-objections referred to in sub-section (4), be accompanied by a fee of ^6[one`
  line `thousand rupees in the case of an appeal filed on or after the 1st day of October, 1998].`
  line
  line `(7) Subject to the provisions of this Act, in hearing and making an order on any appeal under this`
  line `section, the Appellate Tribunal shall exercise the same powers and follow the same procedure as it`
  line `exercises and follows in hearing and making an order on any appeal under the Income-tax Act.`
obj_root_law_sections_16_footnotes:
  string
  line `1. Subs. by Act 29 of 1977, s. 39 and the Fifth Schedule, for " Appellate Assistant Commissioner" (w.e.f. 1-4-1977).`
  line
  line `2. Subs. by Act 29 of 1977, s. 39 and the Fifth Schedule, for "an Appellate Assistant Commissioner" (w.e.f. 1-4-1977).`
  line
  line `3. Subs. by Act 49 of 1991, s. 104, for "Income-tax Officer" (w.e.f. 1-10-1991).`
  line
  line `4. Subs. by Act 49 of 1991, s. 104, for "Income-tax Officer" (w.e.f. 1-10-1991).`
  line
  line `5. Subs. by Act 29 of 1977, s. 39 and the Fifth Schedule, for "Appellate Assistant Commissioner" (w.e.f. 1-4-1977).`
  line
  line `6. Subs. by Act 21 of 1998, s. 79, for "two hundred rupees" (w.e.f. 1-10-1998).`
obj_root_law_sections_17:
  sectionId (35470)
  sectionNo (17)
  orderNo 21
  title `Rectification of mistakes.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_17_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_17_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_2_00017_197445_1517807320626&sectionId=35470&sectionno=17&orderno=21&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_2_00017_197445_1517807320626
obj_root_law_sections_17_content:
  string
  line `(1) With a view to rectifying any mistake apparent from the record,`
  line `the Commissioner, the ^2[Assessing Officer], the ^1[Commissioner (Appeals)] and the Appellate Tribunal`
  line `may, of his, or its, own motion or on an application by the assessee in this behalf, amend any order passed`
  line `by him or it in any proceeding under this Act ^3[within four years from the end of the financial year in`
  line `which such order was passed].`
  line
  line `(2) An amendment which has the effect of enhancing the assessment or reducing a refund or`
  line `otherwise increasing the liability of the assessee shall not be made under this section unless the authority`
  line `concerned has given notice to the assessee of its intention so to do and has allowed the assessee a`
  line `reasonable opportunity of being heard.`
  line
  line `(3) Where an amendment is made under this section, the order shall be passed in writing by the`
  line `authority concerned.`
  line
  line `(4) Subject to the other provisions of this Act, where any such amendment has the effect of reducing`
  line `the assessment, the ^2[Assessing Officer] shall make any refund which may be due to such assessee.`
  line
  line `(5) Where any such amendment has the effect of enhancing the assessment or reducing the refund`
  line `already made, the ^2[Assessing Officer] shall serve on the assessee a notice of demand in the prescribed`
  line `form specifying the sum payable.`
obj_root_law_sections_17_footnotes:
  string
  line `1. Subs. by Act 29 of 1977, s. 39 and the Fifth Schedule, for "Appellate Assistant Commissioner" (w.e.f. 1-4-1977).`
  line
  line `2. Subs. by Act 49 of 1991, s. 105, for "Income-tax Officer" (w.e.f. 1-10-1991).`
  line
  line `3. Subs. by Act 67 of 1984, s. 82, for "within four years of the date on which such order was passed" (w.e.f. 1-10-1984).`
obj_root_law_sections_18:
  sectionId (35471)
  sectionNo (18)
  orderNo 22
  title `Interest-tax deductible in computing total income under the Income-tax Act.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_18_content
  footnotes `1. Subs. by Act 49 of 1991, s. 106, for section 18 (w.e.f. 1-10-1991).`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_2_00017_197445_1517807320626&sectionId=35471&sectionno=18&orderno=22&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_2_00017_197445_1517807320626
obj_root_law_sections_18_content:
  string
  line `^1[18. Interest-tax deductible in computing total income under the Income-tax`
  line `Act.--Notwithstanding anything contained in the Income-tax Act, in computing the income of a credit`
  line `institution chargeable to income-tax under the head "Profits and gains of business or profession" or under`
  line `the head "Income from other sources", the interest-tax payable by the credit institution for any assessment`
  line `year shall be deductible from the income, under the respective heads, of the credit institution assessable`
  line `for that assessment year.]`
obj_root_law_sections_19:
  sectionId (35472)
  sectionNo (19)
  orderNo 23
  title `Revision of order prejudicial to revenue.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_19_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_19_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_2_00017_197445_1517807320626&sectionId=35472&sectionno=19&orderno=23&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_2_00017_197445_1517807320626
obj_root_law_sections_19_content:
  string
  line `(1) The Commissioner may call for and examine the`
  line `record of any proceeding under this Act, and if he considers that any order passed therein by`
  line `the ^1[Assessing Officer] is erroneous in so far as it is prejudicial to the interests of the revenue, he may, after giving the assessee an opportunity of being heard and after making or causing to be made such`
  line `enquiry as he deems necessary, pass such order thereon as the circumstances of the case justify, including`
  line `an order enhancing or modifying the assessment, or cancelling the assessment and directing a fresh`
  line assessment.
  line
  line `^2[Explanation.--For the removal of doubts, it is hereby declared that, for the purposes of this`
  line sub-section,--
  line
  line `(a) "record" shall include and shall be deemed always to have included all records relating to any`
  line `proceeding under this Act available at the time of examination by the Commissioner;`
  line
  line `(b) where any order referred to in this sub-section is the subject matter of any appeal, the power of`
  line `the Commissioner under this sub-section shall extend to all such matters as had not been considered`
  line `and decided in such appeal.]`
  line
  line `^3[(2) No order shall be made under in sub-section (1) after the expiry of two years from the end of the`
  line `financial year in which the order sought to be revised was passed.]`
  line
  line `(3) Notwithstanding anything contained sub-section (2), an order-in revision under this section may`
  line `be passed at anytime in the case of an order which has been passed in consequence of, or to give effect to,`
  line `any finding or direction contained in an order of the Appellate Tribunal ^4[the National Tax Tribunal], the`
  line `High Court or the Supreme Court.`
  line
  line `Explanation.--In computing the period of limitation for the purposes of sub-section (2), ^5[the time`
  line `taken in giving an opportunity to the assessee to be reheard under the proviso to section 129 of the`
  line `Income-tax Act, as applicable to this Act by virtue of section 21 of this Act, and] any period during which`
  line `any proceeding under this section is stayed by an order or injunction of any court shall be excluded.`
obj_root_law_sections_19_footnotes:
  string
  line `1. Subs. by s. 107, ibid., for "Income-tax Officer" (w.e.f. 1-10-1991).`
  line
  line `2. Subs. by Act 49 of 1991, s. 107, for the Explanation (w.e.f. 1-10-1991).`
  line
  line `3. Subs. by Act 67 of 1984, s. 83, for sub-section (2) (w.e.f. 1-10-1984).`
  line
  line `4. Ins. by Act 49 of 2005, s. 30 and the Schedule (w.e.f. 28-12-2005).`
  line
  line `5. Ins. by Act 49 of 1991, s. 107 (w.e.f. 1-10-1991).`
obj_root_law_sections_20:
  sectionId (35473)
  sectionNo (20)
  orderNo 24
  title `Revision of orders by Commissioner.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_20_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_20_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_2_00017_197445_1517807320626&sectionId=35473&sectionno=20&orderno=24&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_2_00017_197445_1517807320626
obj_root_law_sections_20_content:
  string
  line `(1) The Commissioner may, either of his own motion or`
  line `on an application by the assessee for revision, call for the record of any proceeding under this Act which`
  line `has been taken by an ^1[Assessing Officer] ^2*** subordinate to him and may make such enquiry or cause`
  line `such enquiry to be made and, subject to the provisions of this Act, may pass such order thereon, not being`
  line `an order prejudicial to the assessee, as he thinks fit.`
  line
  line `(2) The Commissioner shall not of his own motion revise any order under this section if the order has`
  line `been made more than one year previously.`
  line
  line `(3) In the case of an application for revision under this section by the assessee, the application shall be`
  line `made within one year from the date on which the order in question was communicated to him or the date`
  line `on which he otherwise came to know of it, whichever is earlier:`
  line
  line `Provided that the Commissioner may, if he is satisfied that the assessee was prevented by sufficient`
  line `cause from making the application within that period, admit an application made after the expiry of that`
  line period.
  line
  line `(4) The Commissioner shall not revise any order under this section in the following cases--`
  line
  line `^3[(a) where an appeal against the order lies to the Commissioner (Appeals) but has not been made`
  line `and the time within which such appeal may be made has not expired, or the assessee has not waived`
  line `his right of appeals; or`
  line
  line `(b) where the order has been made the subject of an appeal to the Commissioner (Appeals).]`
  line
  line `(5) Every application by an assessee for revision under this section shall be accompanied by a fee of`
  line `twenty-five rupees.`
  line
  line `^4[(6) On every application by an assessee for revision under this sub-section, made on or after the 1st`
  line `day of October, 1998, an order shall be passed within one year from the end of the financial year in which`
  line `such application is made by the assesse for revision.`
  line
  line `Explanation.--In computing the period of limitation for the purposes of this sub-section, the time`
  line `taken in giving an opportunity to the assessee to be re-heard under the proviso to section 21 and any`
  line `period during which any proceeding under this section is stayed by an order or injunction of any court`
  line `shall be excluded.`
  line
  line `(7) Notwithstanding anything contained in sub-section (6), an order in revision under sub-section (6)`
  line `may be passed at any time in consequence of or to give effect to any finding or direction contained in an`
  line `order of the ^5[Appellate Tribunal, the National Tax Tribunal, the High Court or the Supreme Court].]`
  line
  line `Explanation.--An order by the Commissioner declining to interfere shall, for the purposes of this`
  line `section be deemed not to be an order prejudicial to the assessee.`
  line
  line `^6* * * * *`
obj_root_law_sections_20_footnotes:
  string
  line `1. Subs. by s. 108, ibid., for "Income-tax Officer" (w.e.f. 1-10-1991).`
  line
  line `2. The words "or Appellate Assistant Commissioner" omitted by Act 29 of 1977, s. 39 and the Fifth Schedule (w.e.f. 8-8-1977).`
  line
  line `3. Subs. by s. 39 and the Fifth Schedule, ibid., for clauses (a), (b) and (c) (w.e.f. 8-8-1977).`
  line
  line `4. Ins. by Act 21 of 1998, s. 80 (w.e.f. 1-10-1998).`
  line
  line `5. Subs. by Act 49 of 2005, s. 30 and the Schedule (w.e.f. 28-12-2005).`
  line
  line `6. The Explanation 2 omitted by 29 of 1977, s. 39 and the Fifth Schedule (w.e.f. 8-8-1977).`
obj_root_law_sections_21:
  sectionId (35474)
  sectionNo (21)
  orderNo 25
  title `Application of provisions of Income-tax Act.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_21_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_21_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_2_00017_197445_1517807320626&sectionId=35474&sectionno=21&orderno=25&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_2_00017_197445_1517807320626
obj_root_law_sections_21_content:
  string
  line `The provisions of the following sections and`
  line `Schedules of the Income-tax Act and the Income-tax (Certificate Proceedings) Rules, 1962, as in force`
  line `from time to time, shall apply with necessary modifications as if the said provisions and the rules referred`
  line `to interest-tax instead of to income-tax:--`
  line
  line `^1[2(44) ^2[,119],129,131,132,132A, 132B, 133 to 136 (both inclusive), 138,140,145, 156, 160, 161,`
  line `162, 163, 166, 167, 170, 173, 175, 176, 178, 179, 220 to 227 (both inclusive), 228A, 229, 232, 237 to 245`
  line `(both inclusive), 254 to 262 (both inclusive), 265, 266, 268, 269, 281, 281B, 282, 284, 287, 288, 288A,`
  line `288B, 289 to 293 (both inclusive), the Second Schedule and the Third Schedule:]`
  line
  line `Provided that references in the said provisions and the rules to the "assessee" shall be construed as`
  line `references to an assessee as defined in this Act.`
obj_root_law_sections_21_footnotes:
  string
  line `1. Subs. by Act 49 of 1991, s. 109, for certain figures, brackets, letters and words (w.e.f. 1-10-1991).`
  line
  line `2. Ins. by Act 26 of 1997, s. 60 (w.e.f. 1-10-1991).`
obj_root_law_sections_22:
  sectionId (35475)
  sectionNo (22)
  orderNo 26
  title `Income-tax papers to be available for the purposes of this Act.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_22_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_22_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_2_00017_197445_1517807320626&sectionId=35475&sectionno=22&orderno=26&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_2_00017_197445_1517807320626
obj_root_law_sections_22_content:
  string
  line `(1) Notwithstanding anything`
  line `contained in the Income-tax Act, all information contained in any statement or return made or furnished`
  line `under the provisions of that Act or obtained or collected for the purposes of that Act may be used for the`
  line `purposes of this Act.`
  line
  line `(2) All information contained in any statement or return made or furnished under the provisions of`
  line `this Act or obtained or collected for the purposes of this Act may be used for the purposes of the`
  line `Income-tax Act.`
obj_root_law_sections_22_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_23:
  sectionId (35476)
  sectionNo (23)
  orderNo 27
  title `Failure to comply with notices.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_23_content
  footnotes `1. Subs. by Act 49 of 1991, s. 110, for sections 23 to 26 (w.e.f 1-10-1991).`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_2_00017_197445_1517807320626&sectionId=35476&sectionno=23&orderno=27&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_2_00017_197445_1517807320626
obj_root_law_sections_23_content:
  string
  line `^1[23. Failure to comply with notices.--If any person fails, without reasonable cause, to produce or`
  line `cause to be produced, any accounts or documents required to be produced under section 8, he shall pay by`
  line `way of penalty, a sum which shall not be less than one thousand rupees, but which may extend to`
  line `twenty-five thousand rupees, for each such failure.]`
obj_root_law_sections_24:
  sectionId (35477)
  sectionNo (24)
  orderNo 28
  title `False statements.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_24_content
  footnotes `1. Subs. by Act 49 of 1991, s. 110, for sections 23 to 26 (w.e.f 1-10-1991).`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_2_00017_197445_1517807320626&sectionId=35477&sectionno=24&orderno=28&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_2_00017_197445_1517807320626
obj_root_law_sections_24_content:
  string
  line `^1[24. False statements.--If a person makes a statement in any verification under this Act or any rule`
  line `made thereunder, or delivers an account or statement which is false, and which he either knows or`
  line `believes to be false or does not believe to be true, he shall be punishable with rigorous imprisonment for a`
  line `term which shall not be less than three months but which may extend to seven years and with fine.]`
obj_root_law_sections_25:
  sectionId (35478)
  sectionNo (25)
  orderNo 29
  title `Wilful attempt to evade tax, etc.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_25_content
  footnotes `1. Subs. by Act 49 of 1991, s. 110, for sections 23 to 26 (w.e.f 1-10-1991).`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_2_00017_197445_1517807320626&sectionId=35478&sectionno=25&orderno=29&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_2_00017_197445_1517807320626
obj_root_law_sections_25_content:
  string
  line `^1[25. Wilful attempt to evade tax, etc.--If a person wilfully attempts in any manner whatsoever to`
  line `evade any interest-tax, penalty or interest chargeable or imposable under this Act, he shall, without`
  line `prejudice to any penalty that may be imposable on him under any other provision of this Act, be punishable with rigorous imprisonment for a term which shall not be less than three months but which`
  line `may extend to seven years and with fine.`
  line
  line `Explanation.--For the purposes of this section, a wilful attempt to evade any interest-tax, penalty or`
  line `interest chargeable or imposable under this Act or the payment thereof shall include a case where any`
  line person--
  line
  line `(i) has in his possession or control any books of account or other documents (being books of`
  line `account or other documents relevant to any proceeding under this Act) containing a false entry or`
  line `statement; or`
  line
  line `(ii) makes or causes to be made any false entry or statement in such books of account or other`
  line `documents; or`
  line
  line `(iii) wilfully omits or causes to be omitted any relevant entry or statement in such books of`
  line `account or other documents; or`
  line
  line `(iv) causes any other circumstances to exist which will have the effect of enabling such person to`
  line `evade any interest-tax, penalty or interest chargeable or imposable under this Act or the payment`
  line thereof.]
obj_root_law_sections_26:
  sectionId (35479)
  sectionNo (26)
  orderNo 30
  title `Abetment of false returns, etc.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_26_content
  footnotes `1. Subs. by Act 49 of 1991, s. 110, for sections 23 to 26 (w.e.f 1-10-1991).`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_2_00017_197445_1517807320626&sectionId=35479&sectionno=26&orderno=30&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_2_00017_197445_1517807320626
obj_root_law_sections_26_content:
  string
  line `^1[26. Abetment of false returns, etc.--If a person abets or induces in any manner another person to`
  line `make and deliver any account or a statement or declaration relating to any chargeable interest which is`
  line `false and which he either knows or believes to be false or does not believe to be true or to commit an`
  line `offence under section 25, he shall be punishable with rigorous imprisonment for a term which shall not be`
  line `less than three months but which may extend to seven years and with fine.]`
obj_root_law_sections_26_a:
  sectionId (35480)
  sectionNo 26A
  orderNo 31
  title `Offences by credit institutions.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_26_a_content
  footnotes `1. Subs. by Act 49 of 1991, s. 110, for sections 23 to 26 (w.e.f 1-10-1991).`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_2_00017_197445_1517807320626&sectionId=35480&sectionno=26A&orderno=31&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_2_00017_197445_1517807320626
obj_root_law_sections_26_a_content:
  string
  line `^1[26A. Offences by credit institutions.--(1) Where an offence under this Act has been committed by a`
  line `credit institution every person who, at the time the offence was committed, was in charge of, and was`
  line `responsible to, the credit institution or the conduct of the business of the credit institution as well as the`
  line `credit institution shall be deemed to be guilty of the offence and shall be liable to be proceeded against`
  line `and punished accordingly:`
  line
  line `Provided that nothing contained in this sub-section shall render any such person liable to any`
  line `punishment if he proves that the offence was committed without his knowledge or that he had exercised`
  line `all due diligence to prevent the commission of such offence.`
  line
  line `(2) Notwithstanding anything contained in sub-section (1), where an offence under this Act has been`
  line `committed by a credit institution and it is proved that the offence has been committed with the consent or`
  line `connivance of, or is attributable to any neglect on the part of, any director, manager, secretary or other`
  line `officer of the credit institution, such director, manager, secretary or other officer shall also be deemed to`
  line `be guilty of that offence and shall be liable to be proceeded against and punished accordingly.`
  line
  line `Explanation.--For the purposes of this section, "director", in relation to a co-operative society, means`
  line `any member controlling the affairs thereof.]`
obj_root_law_sections_26_b:
  sectionId (35481)
  sectionNo 26B
  orderNo 32
  title `Institution of proceedings and composition of offences.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_26_b_content
  footnotes `1. Subs. by Act 49 of 1991, s. 110, for sections 23 to 26 (w.e.f 1-10-1991).`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_2_00017_197445_1517807320626&sectionId=35481&sectionno=26B&orderno=32&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_2_00017_197445_1517807320626
obj_root_law_sections_26_b_content:
  string
  line `^1[26B. Institution of proceedings and composition of offences.--(1) A person shall not be`
  line `proceeded against for any offence under section 24 or section 25 or section 26 or for any offence under`
  line `the Indian Penal Code (45 of 1860), except with the previous sanction of the Commissioner or`
  line `Commissioner (Appeals):`
  line
  line `Provided that the Chief Commissioner or, as the case may be, Director General may issue such`
  line `instructions or directions to the aforesaid interest-tax authorities as he may deem fit for institution of`
  line `proceedings under this sub-section.`
  line
  line `(2) Any offence under the sections referred to in sub-section (1) may, either before or after the`
  line `institution of proceedings, be compounded by the Chief Commissioner or Director General.`
  line
  line `Explanation.--For the removal of doubts, it is hereby declared that the power of the Board to issue`
  line `orders, instructions or directions under this Act shall include the power to issue instructions or directions`
  line `(including instructions or directions to obtain the previous approval of the Board) to other interest-tax`
  line `authorities for the proper composition of offences under this section.]`
obj_root_law_sections_26_c:
  sectionId (35482)
  sectionNo 26C
  orderNo 33
  title `Power of credit institutions to vary certain agreements.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_26_c_content
  footnotes `1. Subs. by Act 49 of 1991, s. 110, for sections 23 to 26 (w.e.f 1-10-1991).`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_2_00017_197445_1517807320626&sectionId=35482&sectionno=26C&orderno=33&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_2_00017_197445_1517807320626
obj_root_law_sections_26_c_content:
  string
  line `^1[26C. Power of credit institutions to vary certain agreements.--Notwithstanding anything`
  line `contained in any agreement under which any term loan has been sanctioned by the credit institution`
  line `before the 1st day of October, 1991, it shall be lawful for the credit institution to vary the agreement, so as`
  line `to increase the rate of interest stipulated therein to the extent to which such institution is liable to pay the`
  line `interest-tax under this Act in relation to the amount of interest on the term loan which is due to the credit`
  line institution.
  line
  line `Explanation.--For the purposes of this section, "term loan" means a loan which is not repayable on`
  line demand.]
obj_root_law_sections_27:
  sectionId (35483)
  sectionNo (27)
  orderNo 34
  title `Power to make rules.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_27_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_27_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_2_00017_197445_1517807320626&sectionId=35483&sectionno=27&orderno=34&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_2_00017_197445_1517807320626
obj_root_law_sections_27_content:
  string
  line `(1) The Board may, subject to the control of the Central Government, by`
  line `notification in the Official Gazette, make rules for carrying out the purposes of this Act.`
  line
  line `(2) In particular, and without prejudice to the generality of the foregoing power, such rules may`
  line `provide for all or any of the following matters, namely:--`
  line
  line `(a) the form in which returns under section 7 may be furnished and the manner in which they may`
  line `be verified;`
  line
  line `(b) the form in which appeals under section 15 or section 16 may be filed and the manner in`
  line `which they may be verified;`
  line
  line `(c) the procedure to be followed on applications for rectification of mistakes and applications for`
  line refunds;
  line
  line `(d) any other matter which by this Act is to be, or may be, prescribed.`
  line
  line `(3) The power to make rules conferred by this section shall on the first occasion of the exercise`
  line `thereof include the power to give retrospective effect to the rules or any of them from a date not earlier`
  line `than the date of commencement of this Act.`
  line
  line `(4) The Central Government shall cause every rule made under this section to be laid, as soon as may`
  line `be after it is made, before each House of Parliament while it is in session for a total period of thirty days`
  line `which may be comprised in one session or in two or more successive sessions, and if, before the expiry of`
  line `the session immediately following the session or the successive sessions aforesaid, both Houses agree in`
  line `making any modification in the rule or both Houses agree that the rule should not be made the rule shall`
  line `thereafter have effect only in such modified form or be of no effect, as the case may be; so, however, that`
  line `any such modification or annulment shall be without prejudice to the validity of anything previously done`
  line `under that rule.`
obj_root_law_sections_27_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_28:
  sectionId (35484)
  sectionNo (28)
  orderNo 35
  title `Power to exempt.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_28_content
  footnotes `1. Subs. by Act 49 of 1991, s.111, for "any scheduled bank or any class of scheduled banks" (w.e.f. 1-10-1991).`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_2_00017_197445_1517807320626&sectionId=35484&sectionno=28&orderno=35&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_2_00017_197445_1517807320626
obj_root_law_sections_28_content:
  string
  line `Where the Central Government is of the opinion that it is necessary or`
  line `expedient so to do either in the public interest or having regard to the peculiar circumstances of the case,`
  line `it may, by notification, and subject to conditions, if any, as may be specified in the notification, exempt`
  line `^1[any credit institution or any class of credit institutions or any interest on any category of loans or`
  line `advances] from the levy of interest-tax:`
  line
  line `Provided that no such exemption shall be made except on the recommendation of the Reserve Bank`
  line `of India.`
obj_root_law_sections_29:
  sectionId (35485)
  sectionNo (29)
  orderNo 36
  title `Power to remove difficulty.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_29_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_29_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_2_00017_197445_1517807320626&sectionId=35485&sectionno=29&orderno=36&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_2_00017_197445_1517807320626
obj_root_law_sections_29_content:
  string
  line `^1[(1)] If any difficulty arises in giving effect to the provisions of`
  line `this Act, the Central Government may, by order, not inconsistent with the provisions of this Act, remove`
  line `the difficulty:`
  line
  line `Provided that no such order shall be made after the expiry of a period of two years from the`
  line `commencement of this Act.`
  line
  line `^2[(2) If any difficulty arises in giving effect to the provisions of this Act, as amended by the Finance`
  line `(No.2) Act, 1991(49 of 1991), the Central Government may, by order, do anything not inconsistent with`
  line `such provisions for the purpose of removing the difficulty:`
  line
  line `Provided that no such order shall be made after the expiry of two years from the 1st day of October,`
  line 1991.
  line
  line `(3) Every order made under sub-section (2) shall be laid before each House of Parliament.]`
obj_root_law_sections_29_footnotes:
  string
  line `1. Section 29 renumbered as sub-section (1) thereof by s. 112, ibid. (w.e.f. 1-10-1991).`
  line
  line `2. Ins. by s. 112, ibid. (w.e.f. 1-10-1991).`
